properties.author: Kevin Stadler
properties.name: Polar bear image archive
properties.description: Minimalist project for test purposes. This project is functionally complete, but does not necessarily make sense. Please do not regard it as a serious case study. It is for testing only.

basis.mandate: Preserve precious polar bear pictures. Preserve their accessability and authenticity without compromise in terms of qualitiy for access over the web.
basis.planningPurpose: Develop a strategy for preservation actions and document reasons for decisions

collectionProfile.description: Two samples should be sufficient, because the collection is extremely homogenous

record.originalTechnicalEnvironment: Picture taken with a digital camera, resized using Application X on Windows

record.description: manipulated picture of a cute polar bear
record.originalTechnicalEnvironment: Picture taken with a digital camera, resized and manipulated using Application Y on Linux

requirementsDefinition.description: We are interested in keeping the images as unaltered as possible as well as a simple and cheap migration process.

alternative.name: TIFF (tool A)
alternative.description: Convert to TIFF using the well-tested and expensive tool 'A'

alternative.name: TIFF (tool B)
alternative.description: Convert to TIFF/4 using this new tool named 'B'

alternative.name: GIF (tool C)
alternative.description: Convert to GIF using the well-tested tool 'C'

alternative.name: PNG (tool D)
alternative.description: Convert to PNG using the well-tested tool 'D'

decision.reason: Interesting services for migration are available, emulation is not considered feasible, resources are sufficient: we can continue with the planning procedure

transformation.comment: The limit for the process cost was decided to be 150 per picture in the last polar-bear-enthusiasts-association-meeting. A complex migration process would be unacceptable as well.
